<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,258,895]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,834,859]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can readily be distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1048,1179,834,859]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Evacanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1048,1179,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Evacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the subcontinent by the unpolished, wrinkled disc of the crown and by the peculiar shape of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
